This var is sometimes exposed to user asking them to alter default naming pattern via
local($mx::NameManager) = mx->name->Prefix("prefix_");
This is consistent with local($mx::AttrScope) = mx->AttrScope(...);
and local($mx::Context) = mx->gpu(1); 
which is in its turn consistent with the python examples.

So the reason I did this is because when I was looking at the code 
```
            if method == 'HEAD':
                raise response_error.head(bucket_name, object_name)
            elif method == 'GET':
                raise response_error.get(bucket_name, object_name)
            elif method == 'POST':
                raise response_error.post(bucket_name, object_name)
            elif method == 'PUT':
                raise response_error.put(bucket_name, object_name)
            elif method == 'DELETE':
                raise response_error.delete(bucket_name, object_name)
            else:
                raise ValueError('Unsupported method returned'
                                 ' error: {0}'.format(response.status))
```
And i thought to myself why? Honestly there's a lot of questionable things in the code and I wish I could do a whole rewrite of minio-py.

@mkhorton I think it'd be better to do this in a `Runner`'s `processor`. There's a `filter(None, chunk)` of processed items before handing off to `update_targets` in [`maggma.runner.SerialProcessor`](https://github.com/materialsproject/maggma/blob/68e09b65ba6852854428e4ada2380413b6270b51/maggma/runner.py#L63), but it looks like similar filtering got left out in @shyamd's refactor of [`maggma.runner.MultiprocProcessor`](https://github.com/materialsproject/maggma/blob/68e09b65ba6852854428e4ada2380413b6270b51/maggma/runner.py#L203) to use `Pool.imap`. I think it'd be best to filter for `None`s there, e.g. passing `list(filter(None, items))` to the `update_targets` call there instead of `items`.

Also, it's okay now, but in future it'd be cleaner to have this as a separate small PR because it's a separate issue than renaming Schema to Validator.

Thanks for discovering this!

Perhaps something along the lines of to avoid duplication of the needs_permission logic:

```python
def need_permissions(factory, action):
    """"Get permission for buckets or abort."""
    def decorator_builder(f):
        @wraps(f)
        def decorate(*args, **kwargs):
            permission = factory(kwargs, action)
            if permission is not None and not permission.can():
                if current_user.is_authenticated:
                    abort(403,
                          'You do not have a permission for this action')
                abort(401)
            return f(*args, **kwargs)
        return decorate
    return decorator_builder


need_bucket_collection_permission = partial(
    need_permission, 
    lambda kwargs, action: current_bucket_collection_permission_factory(action)
)

need_bucket_permission = partial(
    need_permission, 
    lambda kwargs, action: current_bucket_permission_factory(kwargs['bucket'], action=action)
)

need_objects_permission = partial(
    need_permission, 
    lambda kwargs, action: current_bucket_collection_permission_factory(kwargs['bucket'], kwargs['object'], action=action)
)
```
